DOC.TEXT:
   Here are the winners from Thursday
night's 21st Annual Gospel Music Association Dove Awards:
   Steven Curtis Chapman, artist of the year;
   Steven Curtis Chapman, male vocalist of the year;
   Sandi Patti, female vocalist of the year;
   BeBe and CeCe Winans, group of the year;
   David Mullen, new artist of the year;
   Steven Curtis Chapman, songwriter of the year;
   ``Thank You,'' Ray Boltz, song of the year;
   ``His Strength Is Perfect,'' Steven Curtis Chapman,
inspirational recorded song of the year;
   ``I Can See the Hand,'' The Cathedrals, southern gospel recorded
song of the year;
   ``'Tis So Sweet to Trust in Jesus,'' Amy Grant, country recorded
song of the year;
   ``With My Whole Heart,'' BeBe and CeCe Winans, contemporary
black gospel recorded song of the year;
   ``Wonderful,'' Beau Williams, traditional black gospel recorded
song of the year;
   ``Triumphant Return,'' White Cross, metal album of the year;
   ``The Way Home,'' Russ Taff, rock album of the year;
   ``Heaven,'' BeBe and CeCe Winans, contemporary album of the year;
   ``The Mission,'' Steve Green, inspirational album of the year;
   ``One of Several Possible Musiks,'' Kerry Livgren, instrumental
album of the year;
   ``I Just Started Living,'' The Cathedrals, southern gospel album
of the year;
   ``Heirloom,'' Heirloom, country album of the year;
   ``Saints in Praise,'' West Angeles Church of God in Christ Mass
Choir, traditional black gospel album of the year;
   ``Our Hymns,'' various artists, praise and worship album of the
year;
   ``Friends Forever-Part II,'' Billy Sprague, musical album of the
year;
   ``Petra Praise,'' Jackson Design, recorded music packaging of
the year;
   ``I Miss the Way,'' Michael W. Smith, short form music video of
the year;
   ``On Fire,'' Petra, long form music video of the year;
   ``In Your Face,'' Shout, metal recorded song of the year;
   ``The River Unbroken,'' Russ Taff, rock recorded song of the
year;
   ``Heaven,'' BeBe and CeCe Winans, contemporary recorded song of
the year;
   ``Will You Be Ready?'' Commissioned, contemporary black gospel
album of the year;
   ``The Acappella Collection,'' The Greg Nelson Singers, chorale
collection of the year;
   ``The Friendship Company,'' Sandi Patti, children's music album
of the year.

